<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Unit_731&amp;action=edit&amp;section=34" title="Edit section: Accounts">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Accounts</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.centurychina.com/wiihist/confess/demondoc.html" class="external text" title="http://www.centurychina.com/wiihist/confess/demondoc.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Army Doctor</i></a>&#160;— a firsthand account by Yuasa Ken.</li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Articles" id="Articles"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Unit_731&amp;action=edit&amp;section=35" title="Edit section: Articles">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Articles</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://people.bu.edu/wwildman/WeirdWildWeb/courses/thth/projects/thth_projects_2003_parkeun.htm" class="external text" title="http://people.bu.edu/wwildman/WeirdWildWeb/courses/thth/projects/thth_projects_2003_parkeun.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>Theodicy - through the Case of “Unit 731”</i></a>&#160;— by Eun Park (2003).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.csmonitor.com/2001/0820/p1s3-woap.html" class="external text" title="http://www.csmonitor.com/2001/0820/p1s3-woap.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Why the past still separates China and Japan</i></a>&#160;— by Robert Marquand (2001), <i>Christian Science Monitor</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/english/doc/2005-05/06/content_439768.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/english/doc/2005-05/06/content_439768.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>China recalls germ warfare experiments</i></a>&#160;— Agencies (2005), <i>China Daily</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://users.westnet.gr/~cgian/shinozuka.htm" class="external text" title="http://users.westnet.gr/~cgian/shinozuka.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>Ex-Japanese Soldier Deemed War Criminal</i></a>&#160;— by Michael Zielenziger (1998), <i>Houston Chronicle</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200508/s1437314.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200508/s1437314.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>US paid for Japanese human germ warfare data</i></a>&#160;— <i>Australian Broadcasting Corporation News Online</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/elsewhere/journalist/story/0,7792,1338296,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.guardian.co.uk/elsewhere/journalist/story/0,7792,1338296,00.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Japan's sins of the past</i></a>&#160;— by Justin McCurry (2004), <i>The Guardian</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2002/08/28/1030508070534.html" class="external text" title="http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2002/08/28/1030508070534.html" rel="nofollow"><i>The Asian Auschwitz of Unit 731</i></a>&#160;— by Shane Green (2002), <i>The Age</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/articles/news/news.html?in_article_id=439776&amp;in_page_id=1770" class="external text" title="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/articles/news/news.html?in_article_id=439776&amp;in_page_id=1770" rel="nofollow"><i>Doctors of Depravity</i></a> - by Christopher Hudson (2007), <i>the Daily Mail</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.repubblica.it/online/cronaca/virustre/fabbrica/fabbrica.html" class="external text" title="http://www.repubblica.it/online/cronaca/virustre/fabbrica/fabbrica.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Orrori e misteri dell'Unità 731, la "fabbrica" dei batteri killer</i></a>&#160;— by Marco Lupis (2003), <i>La Repubblica</i> (Italy).</li>
</ul>
